cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.PL

The paper deals with a specific type of number theory based on computability logic, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). It also discusses complexity constraints and tricomplexity classes, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the extraction of solutions from proofs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses parameterized/schematic versions of the theory, which could be seen as a programming language (cs.PL) for clarithmetic.
